File: COVID-19 test. AFP/Jens Schlueter JOHANNESBURG - COVID-19 cases continue to climb as 9,445 new cases have been recorded. The cumulative number of cases in South Africa is now 921,922. READ: Mkhize says new COVID-19 variant driving second wave  At least 793,914 people have recovered from the virus. The health department said 152 people have died due to the virus since the last report, mostly in the Eastern Cape. The total number of people who have succumbed to COVID-19 in South Africa now stands at 24,691. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. Today the cumulative number of cases stands at 921,922. pic.twitter.com/D8DDKXHZJf